title: Five things to know about Bengals win over Bills
text:
Posted: 7:27 p.m. Sunday, Oct. 18, 2015 Five things to know about Bengals win over Bills Staff Writer ORCHARD PARK, N.Y. — 
Cincinnati quarterback Andy Dalton had another big game, wide receiver Marvin Jones had the most catches in his career and the defense did just enough to keep the Bengals perfect. 
Sunday’s 34-21 victory at Ralph Wilson Stadium sends Cincinnati into its bye week with a perfect 6-0 record that equals the best start in franchise history.
